    "description": "A polygonal Roman-era temple probably associated with an ancient spring. The site, now a modern park, was located at a place known in the 20th century as Aron and Lescudillier, immediately southwest of the center of the modern French commune of Aurillac (Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes).",
    "details": "<p>The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: Aron, Cm. Aurillac</p>",
